\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
CJIS External Provider Oversight
\series default
:
 The IT Director (as LASO) shall ensure that vendor agreements for external system services with access to CJI authorize the CJIS Systems Agency (CSA),
 the CJIS Systems Officer (CSO),
 their designated auditors,
 and authorized County representatives to conduct audits at minimum triennially,
 conduct unannounced security inspections,
 and require evidence of control compliance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Fingerprint-Based Record Check
\series default
:
 The IT Director (as LASO) shall ensure that,
 prior to any grant of logical access or unescorted physical access to CJI,
 all vendor personnel undergo a state of residency and national fingerprint-based record check adjudicated by the CSA or the State Identification Bureau (SIB) in accordance with CJIS Security Policy v6.0 PS-3 (Personnel Screening).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Vendor Personnel Notification
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure vendor agreements require vendor notification to the IT Director or designee within one (1) business day of any transfer or termination of vendor personnel holding County credentials,
 badges,
 or system privileges,
 and prior to separation where planned.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Subcontractor Flow-Down
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure vendor agreements prohibit the vendor from engaging subcontractors or sub-processors with access to County data,
 network connectivity,
 or CJI exposure without prior affirmative written approval from the IT Director.
 Absence of an affirmative written response from the IT Director shall not constitute approval.
 Vendor agreements shall require contractual flow-down of all applicable County obligations —
 including security controls,
 incident notification,
 audit rights,
 personnel screening,
 data handling,
 and destruction requirements —
 to any approved subcontractor.
 The prime vendor shall remain fully liable for subcontractor compliance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Vendor Incident Notification
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure vendor agreements require vendor notification to the Information Operations Department of any suspected or confirmed incident affecting County systems or County data.
 Contract terms shall establish the following windows:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
CJI Branch
\series default
:
 If CJI may be impacted,
 vendor notification shall occur no later than one (1) hour after discovery,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0 IR-6 (Incident Reporting).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Non-CJI Branch
\series default
:
 For all other incidents affecting County systems or data,
 vendor notification shall occur no later than twenty-four (24) calendar hours after discovery.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Monitoring and Service Oversight
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure vendor contracts provide County monitoring and review access to security operational information through one or more of the following:
 automated access to vendor audit logs,
 annual third-party assurance reports (e.g.,
 SOC 2 Type II),
 or integration with County-designated security monitoring infrastructure.
 For vendors handling CJI,
 contracts shall also incorporate CJIS monitoring requirements consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0 SA-9 (External System Services).
\end_layout

