\begin_layout Subsubsection*
6.10 Vendor Records Retention
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The IT Director shall ensure vendor records are retained in the County-designated contract repository,
 with a corresponding entry in the System of Engagement linking each record to the applicable vendor engagement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Contract-Class Records
\series default
:
 Executed vendor contracts,
 CJIS Security Addenda,
 CJIS Security Addendum Certifications,
 and Information Exchange Agreements shall be retained for six (6) fiscal years from termination or completion of the contract in accordance with NRS 239.125,
 NAC 239.155,
 and LRDA 20070474 (Contracts and Agreements).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Vendor-File-Class Records
\series default
:
 Vendor risk assessments,
 security questionnaires,
 independent attestations,
 fingerprint-based record check documentation,
 and vendor performance evidence shall be retained for three (3) fiscal years from the fiscal year to which they pertain in accordance with NRS 239.125,
 NAC 239.155,
 and LRDA 20070378 (Vendor Files).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Retrievability
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure that executed contracts,
 addenda,
 and Information Exchange Agreements are retrievable within one (1) business day of request,
 consistent with the retrieval standard in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.14"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 §6.5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Legal Hold
\series default
:
 Retention schedules shall be suspended on any record subject to a legal hold.
 Records shall not be destroyed while a legal hold is in effect.
\end_layout

